Instructions

In your own words, describe an algorithm for baking cookies. Assume that you have a large number of hungry friends, so you'll want to produce several batches of cookies!


Solution

- Take out eggs
- Take out butter
- Take out sugar
- Take out flour
- Take out chocolate chips
- Take out a large mixing bowl
- Measure out amounts for each of the ingredients according to favorite chocolate chip cookie recipe.
- Follow instructions for making one batch of dough according the the recipe chosen.
- Repeat previous step two more times.
- Place first batch in the oven for about 15 to 20 mintues (or until golden brown) at 350 degrees Fahrenheight.
- Repeat previous step two more times for other two batches.
- Serve with preferred type of milk or other drink.
